Package: focuson
Title: Inference on Scalar Functions of Model Parameters
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: c(person(given = "Ioannis", family = "Kosmidis", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "ioannis.kosmidis@warwick.ac.uk", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1556-0302")),
             person(given = "Davide", family = "Benussi", role = c("aut"), email = "davide.benussi@studenti.unipd.it"))
Description: Provides methods for estimation and inference for user-specified parameters of interest from fitted model objects through the `focus()` method. Estimation can be performed using mean or median bias correction, and inference is based on Wald-type confidence intervals using delta-method standard errors or HulC confidence intervals <doi:10.1093/jrsssb/qkad134>.
